# Backend (NestJS)

Follow `docs/API_STANDARDS.md` and `docs/CODING_GUIDELINES.md`.

## Layout

`modules/<feature>/{presentation,application,domain,infrastructure}`

- Controllers: validate DTOs, call use cases, map errors — no business rules.
- Use cases: authorize, orchestrate ports, audit.
- Repositories/MCP adapters live in infrastructure only.

## API

- Versioned `/v1` · problem+json errors · correlation IDs · Idempotency-Key on mutating POSTs.
- Never return Prisma entities raw — map to response DTOs.

## Example

```typescript
// ✅ use case + port
await this.applyLeave.execute(cmd, ctx);
// ❌ Prisma inside controller
```
